The government had planned to borrow 159.2 billion kronor this year.
Thanks to better-than-expected savings in the state budget, the ministry reduced the projected amount to 152.8 billion kronor.
The state debt of the Czech Republic rose by the end of September to 842.7 billion kronor.
During the nine months of this year it therefore increased by 40.2 billion kronor.
However, as of June, it has decreased by 13.4 billion kronor.
