The debt of the state is constituted by the debts of the central government and is generated mainly by the accumulation of deficits in the state budget.
Government debt is financed by treasury bonds, pension securities, direct loans or, for example, loans to the European Investment Bank.
The state's domestic debt has risen this year from 38.5 billion to 719.4 billion kronor.
The state’s external debt has risen this year from 1.7 billion kronor to 123.3 billion kronor.
