Better than expected
This follows the 2007 government debt financing and management strategy that the government had planned to borrow C$159.2 billion this year.
However, at the beginning of September, thanks to better-than-expected savings in the state budget, the ministry reduced the projected amount to 152.8 billion kronor.
The sum is essentially the deficit of the state budget, which is clearly going to reach 76 billion kronor this year, instead of the 91.3 billion kronor initially planned.
Secondly, these are the maximum sources planned for the Czech Consolidation Agency, namely 13.3 billion kroner, the 10 billion reserve for pension payments, the financing of 43 billion kroner of government bonds and the repayments of loans from the European Investment Bank amounting to 1.8 billion kroner.
