What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible claims, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, driver's license seniority, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use that is made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the right model.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is embodied in an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the award and in return becomes liable for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is determined by taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driver's license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the likelihood of an accident, the higher the odds to pay.
For this reason, people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower claim rate than their caution.
Similarly, using censuses, companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of having an accident.
By increasing the frequency, the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must carefully study the situation to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will explain the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face a variety of disadvantages when entering into an insurance contract at an affordable price, such as low driving experience and driver's license seniority.
Although the ideal way to be well insured is to insure at all risks, other, more economical options exist.
The more forward-thinking drivers can opt for all-risk insurance with deductibles, so that they get insurance coverage at all-risk but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
“The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be determined based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount,” Luis Noguera, the head in Spain of First Europa, online insurance mediator, said in a statement.
Another option is extended third party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fires and loss of the vehicle.
One piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25 try to be cautious and avoid claims as much as possible, since this will have an impact on the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic fare that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
“Bonus and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses,” Noguera explains.
Beyond the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers to enter into an insurance contract, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is best to choose all-risk insurance with deductible.
"Normally young people can not take advantage of the experience previously acquired after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable that he negotiates insurance at all risks, as long as his economic situation allows it.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest claims rate, because the surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance at any risk with deductible (may be 300 euros), or an extended third party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have more casual driving and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchises," Noguera said.
For pensioners, insurance at any risk with deductible is preferable (being this one of 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is fundamental to study properly the insurance that suits us best according to our personal situation.
